&lt;p&gt;Imagine you‚Äôre the newly hired junior associate of tech recruiting.  Your client asked for a rockstar developer but you know nothing, so you Google ‚Äúweb development‚Äù.   Nothing useful there except a dated Wikipedia entry.  How about ‚Äúmodern web development‚Äù?  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ok, now you‚Äôre looking for someone who knows a few things: advanced CSS, a JavaScript framework (not jQuery), API interactions, performance optimization‚Ä¶  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What if you, the (aspiring/junior/mid/senior) developer, don‚Äôt know all those things?  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gatsbyjs.org/&quot;&gt;Gatsby&lt;/a&gt; is a modern development framework that includes all the above:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚úÖ Javascript (React)&lt;br&gt;
‚úÖ Prebuilt CSS (CSS-in-JS)&lt;br&gt;
‚úÖ API reusability (GraphQL)&lt;br&gt;
‚úÖ Blazing performance (Webpack/PWA)  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Why Gatsby?&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/campbell-boulanger-porsche-0e7ff6d71dae2ddd599e9a7631c59a31-8a0ff.jpg&quot;
