&lt;p&gt;My SmartDesk is the &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shelby_Mustang&quot;&gt;Eleanor&lt;/a&gt; of my office, the Picasso in my gallery, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GG-uE0Iewdo&quot;&gt;Wagyu&lt;/a&gt; I‚Äôll remember forever.  Seriously though, this desk is awesome.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cost-effective?  Check.  Multiple positions?  Check.  Attractive colors?  Check.  What‚Äôs not to like?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spring for the wide (70x30) version and thank me later.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01F704KHQ&quot;&gt;Viva Ergonomic Drafting Chair&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this was Buzzfeed, I‚Äôd tell you the only possible standing desk chair is a &lt;a href=&quot;http://store.hermanmiller.com/office/stools/aeron-work-stool/2197386.html&quot;&gt;Herman Miller Aeron&lt;/a&gt;. Make sure you add the La Croix dispenser option for the optimal experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortunately, this isn‚Äôt Buzzfeed.  This standing desk chair leans back, tilts forward, and goes up &amp;#x26; down.  It feels nice on your butt and slides easily on a carpet mat.  Buy some &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00CEZKFO0&quot;&gt;armrest replacements&lt;/a&gt; so the eventual rubber cracks don‚Äôt annoy you more than Slack does.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16824011141&quot;&gt;Acer Frameless 24‚Äù Monitor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
