&lt;p&gt;Show me a product that works after you pull the cable out and I‚Äôll probably buy it.  This keyboard looks nice (white or black), charges off ambient light, and lays completely flat when you need to smash it.  Make sure you get the Mac version (or Windows, respectively).  Also, you‚Äôll probably die before the mouse battery does.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I did get some wrist pain with this setup, so I bought an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B01M11FLUJ&quot;&gt;ergonomic wrist rest&lt;/a&gt; and haven‚Äôt had a problem since.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01MCRVPO6&quot;&gt;Plantronics Backbeat Pro 2 SE Headphones&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Headphones are pretty important if you roam through coffee shops, book a coworking space, or share an office wall with a teething infant.  These have active noise cancellation, so if you want music OR silence‚Ä¶ voil√†.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00NQ1CLTI&quot;&gt;Brother Monochrome Laser Printer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You never know when you need to print something, so you might as well get a cheap printer that never runs out of toner, right?&lt;/p&gt;
