&lt;p&gt;My office doesn‚Äôt have room for an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.businessinsider.com/google-sleep-pods-2010-6&quot;&gt;EnergyPod&lt;/a&gt;, but if my brain can‚Äôt function after lunch, it‚Äôs time for a &lt;a href=&quot;https://medium.com/swlh/pro-tips-for-power-napping-like-a-king-c62db629d78&quot;&gt;caffeine nap&lt;/a&gt;.  On average, we fall asleep in &lt;a href=&quot;https://aasm.org/resources/practiceparameters/pp_msltmwt.pdf&quot;&gt;10-15 minutes&lt;/a&gt;, so I set alarms for 20 minutes later (no snoozing!) and start drinking water or coffee as soon as I wake up.&lt;/p&gt;
